# AIPM Blueprint Traceability (Prompt 05+)

When authoring or editing files under `Engineering-Blueprint/05-Enterprise-Information-Model/` through `Engineering-Blueprint/25-Templates/`:

## Permanent rule (ADR-GOV-003)

**No new concept may be introduced unless traceable to an approved capability (CAP-###), information concept (CON-###, after EIM), requirement (FR/NFR/SC/CON), constitutional article (PC-AIPM-001), or accepted ADR.**

If a genuinely new concept is required:
1. Stop and draft a new ADR in `02-Architecture/ADR/`
2. Get it accepted and indexed in `00-Governance/ADR-Index.md`
3. Only then add the concept to the blueprint document

## Domain stability (ADR-GOV-007)

After DM-AIPM-001 approval: no new aggregates, identity changes, or CMD/EVT without ADR. All `07+` docs derive from Domain Model.

## Canonical concept rule (ADR-GOV-006)

Every `CON-###` has exactly one canonical definition and one canonical owner. No duplicate concepts or undocumented overlap.

## Layer order (ADR-GOV-005)

```
04 BCM → 05 EIM → 06 DDD → 07 Events → 08 State Machines → 09+ Technology
```

## Do not modify locked documents

SRS, SAD, Constitution, BCM, EIM, DM, ADR-TECH-001, and locked ADRs are immutable unless user explicitly requests amendment via new ADR.

## ID conventions

- Information layer: `CON-###`, `REL-###`, `IDL-###`
- Application layer: `BC-##`, `AGG-###`, `ENT-###`, `VO-###`, `CMD-###`, `EVT-###`, `POL-###`, `SVC-###`, `VAL-###`, `DDL-###`

## Mandatory linkages (ADR-GOV-004)

- Every state transition in `08-State-Machines/` must reference `CMD-###` and/or `EVT-###`
- Every `CMD-###` that mutates state must declare postcondition transitions
- Every DDD aggregate/entity must trace to `CON-###` from EIM

## Quality gates

Before APPROVED: pass all applicable gates in `21-Quality/Document-Quality-Gates.md`.

## Authoring specs

- Methodology: `00-Governance/Blueprint-Authoring-Methodology.md`
- Prompt 05 (EIM): `05-Enterprise-Information-Model/PROMPT-05-SPECIFICATION.md`
- Prompt 06 (DDD): `06-Domain-Model/PROMPT-06-SPECIFICATION.md`

## Technology stack (ADR-TECH-001 — LOCKED)

- Backend: C# / .NET 9 / ASP.NET Core 9
- Database: PostgreSQL 16+; cache: Redis; vectors: pgvector
- Messaging: RabbitMQ → Kafka migration path
- Frontend: Next.js (TypeScript)
- Cloud primary: Azure

Changes require ADR-TECH-002+. Supersedes ADR-008 runtime choices (ADR-008 file unchanged).
